  "prompt": "How long does it take to transfer money through SBI ATM, from one SBI account to another SBI account?",
  "response": "When transferring money from one SBI account to another SBI account using an SBI ATM, the transaction is typically **instantaneous**. The funds are credited to the recipient's account immediately after the transaction is completed. \n\nHowever, to ensure the transfer is successful, follow these steps:\n\n1. Insert your SBI ATM card into the SBI ATM.\n2. Enter your PIN.\n3. Select the \"Fund Transfer\" or \"Account to Account Transfer\" option.\n4. Choose \"SBI to SBI Transfer\" or a similar option.\n5. Enter the recipient's account number.\n6. Confirm the details and complete the transaction.\n\nOnce the transaction is confirmed, the money should reflect in the recipient's account right away. If you encounter any issues, it\u2019s advisable to check with SBI customer care or visit your nearest branch.",
